io.github.utk003.util.func

Interface LambdaN<R,T>

  • Type Parameters:
    R - The return type of this lambda function
    T - The type of the parameters of this lambda function
    Functional Interface:
    This is a functional interface and can therefore be used as the assignment target for a lambda expression or method reference.

    @FunctionalInterface
public interface LambdaN<R,T>
    Represents a lambda function which takes in N parameters of type T and returns an object of type R.

    This is a FunctionalInterface whose functional method is get(Object[]).

    Since:
    1.0.3
    Version:
    January 13, 2021
    Author:
    Utkarsh Priyam (utk003)
